<p>That's it.</p>
<p>Our controller doesn't know or care <em>how</em> we were authenticated: it just cares that
<code>$this-&gt;getUser()</code> returns the correct user object.</p>
<p>Run the test again.</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./vendor/bin/phpunit --filter testPOSTProgrammerWorks</div></code></pre>
<p>It still passes! Welcome to our beautiful JWT authentication system. Now, time to
lock down every endpoint: I don't want other users messing with my code battlers.</p>

    
